Title: Predictive Modeling Using Machine Learning

Objective:
Build a machine learning model to predict salary category.

Dataset:
Employee dataset containing age, department, salary, experience, and performance score.

Data Preprocessing:
- Removed duplicates
- Filled missing values
- Encoded categorical data

Algorithm Used:
Decision Tree Classifier

Model Evaluation:
Accuracy Score: 85% (example)

Visualization:
Confusion matrix generated using Seaborn and Matplotlib.

Conclusion:
The model successfully predicted salary categories with good accuracy.
